net.metro.systemobjects.periodobjects

Class TimePeriod

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.metro.systemobjects.periodobjects.TimePeriod
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimePeriod>

    public class TimePeriod
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TimePeriod>
    Object to describe a duration between two Time objects. It contains several static TimePeriod objects which should be used in the program, but it can also be instantiated in order to compare one TimePeriod with another.
    Author:
    Sean Harger
